        "signature": "-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\nwsBcBAABCAAQBQJb4irNCRBK7hj4Ov3rIwAAdHIIAAr+ZSa1/Aun61E3VzeWl6Yk\nWK75nDPxZ35SKXd+5LGKoFJpBoNNkbjdU5SpitNFy6BOpSzfVGNmbIrUexhP/p3m\n+rYCzLeGQiizkhcH+n5WuxvOVdBdOINw2tHUTZUo5xMSIwu+JCk0vPmAYS8pDLMg\nprtvI1pgFUtu8l4IrtXNj1S+yP+2mzrp+Nn1UV5TgAOyTTrNj6UiIej73aRot2ZL\nyC4fqbqFWm1SdnlkdbUUQEiPimJ799Gsq89O/ih16QVqZjDARdo3nZk4tY8tdbBL\n6dnrhD95TBBIbcP9oe8nIxBTNB7fSkEB7+9Nc1eOlVv+gPsDjzV3Ee00IFOzCoQ=\n=lGgJ\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----\n",
        "payload": "tree a658bdde94f645aace05050cf28f1ae9745213c2\nparent d864e45730be82879abe9c096c4d577975fdda7d\nauthor rodasmith <rodasmith@users.noreply.github.com> 1541548749 +0000\ncommitter GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1541548749 +0000\n\nallow writes to /etc/bitcoin\n\nThe hardening measure `ProtectSystem=full` makes /etc read-only along with its subdirectories, including /etc/bitcoin. That prevents bitcoind from launching successfully when it finds it cannot write to /etc/bitcoin/debug.log and such.\r\n\r\nExempt /etc/bitcoin with the directive `ReadWritePaths=/etc/bitcoin`"
